Hire a `BizOps Generalist` or `Chief of Staff to Founder`, not a “head of” anything.

What to optimize for:
- `3-6 years` at an early-stage startup
- Has done ops, analytics, customer support triage, recruiting coordination, and sales support
- Strong in `spreadsheets, writing, CRM/admin tools, and process design`
- High agency, low ego, fast learner

What they should own:
- Weekly priorities and follow-through
- KPI dashboard and reporting
- Sales collateral, CRM hygiene, proposal support
- Customer support triage and handoff
- Recruiting ops: sourcing coordination, scheduling, scorecards
- Basic cross-functional project management

Why this is the cheapest/easiest hire:
- One mid-level generalist is cheaper than a strategist or multiple specialists
- They onboard faster if you give them clear systems, not fuzzy “own everything”
- They can absorb founder chaos and turn it into repeatable process

How to make it work:
- Give them a `30/60/90-day scorecard`
- Start with a `paid trial project` for 1-2 weeks
- Hire for `execution quality and judgment`, not impressive titles
- Keep strategy as “support founder decision-making,” not “set company vision”

Avoid:
- Senior strategy candidates
- Pure analysts
- Pure support/recruiting specialists
- Anyone who says they “lead” but can’t show hands-on output

If you want one job title to post, use: `Founder's Associate / BizOps Generalist`.Hire a `BizOps Generalist` or `Chief of Staff to Founder`, not a “head of” anything.

